reut2-015.sgm, STOLTENBERG NOT SURPRISED BY DOLLAR REACTION, West German Finance Minister GerhardStoltenberg said he was not surprised by the overnight declineof the dollar in foreign exchange markets.    Speaking briefly with reporters before entering a meetingof the International Monetary Fund he said, These minormovements don't really affect us."    The dollar declined in the initial reaction to a statementby the Group of Seven industrial countries reaffirming theirParis agreement in February to maintain their currencies aroundcurrent levels. Reuter&#3;

