reut2-015.sgm, FIRE AT TATE/LYLE LONDON JETTY HALTS UNLOADING, No raw sugar is being unloaded at Tateand Lyles refinery at Silvertown on the River Thames followinga fire yesterday afternoon, Tate and Lyle Plc said.    The fire destroyed a large sector of the main conveyor fromthe raw sugar jetty to the weighhouse.    The company said it is not yet known how long the jettywill be out of use but it hoped that by tomorrow unloading ofthe bulk carrier Mykon Wave will be able to continue usingtemporary arrangements, Tate and Lyle said.    The Mykon Wave arrived in the port recently with about18,300 tonnes of bulk sugar from Maputo in Swaziland. About1,600 tonnes remain to be discharged.    Five other ships loaded with raw sugar are awaiting atSilvertown to be discharged, Tate and Lyle added. Reuter&#3;
