reut2-015.sgm, EXPORTS OTHER THAN COFFEE RISE SHARPLY IN COLOMBIA, Colombian exports other than coffee rose55 pct in January compared with the same period last year,figures from the government statistics institute show.    Non-coffee exports amounted to 180.8 mln dlrs fob comparedwith 147.5 mln dlrs for coffee, a drop of 42 pct from lastyear.    The trade balance registered a 35 mln dlr surplus, comparedwith a 56 mln dlr surplus in January 1986.    The national planning department forecast that in 1987coffee, Colombia's traditional major export, will account foronly one third of total exports, or about 1.5 billion dlrs. REUTER&#3;
