reut2-015.sgm, EXPORT BONUS WHEAT FLOUR TO IRAQ --USDA, The Commodity Credit Corporation(CCC) accepted a bid for an export bonus to cover a sale of12,500 tonnes of U.S. wheat flour to Iraq, the U.S. AgricultureDepartment said.    The department said the bonus awarded was 105.82 dlrs pertonne and the wheat flour is for shipment July 1-10, 1987.    The bonus was awarded to The Pillsbury Company and will bepaid in the form of commodities from CCC stocks.    An additional 150,000 tonnes of wheat flour is stillavailable to Iraq under the Export Enhancement Programinitiative announced January 7, 1987, the department said. Reuter&#3;
